Name: mkc
Version: 0.0.3
Summary: Initialize a C++ project.
Home-page: https://www.bitbucket.org/johannestaas/mkc
Author: Johan Nestaas
Author-email: johannestaas@gmail.com
License: GPLv3+
Description: mkc
        ===
        
        Initialize a C++ project with cmake boilerplate.
        
        Installation
        ------------
        
        From PyPI::
        
            $ pip install mkc
        
        From the project root directory::
        
            $ python setup.py install
        
        Usage
        -----
        
        Simply run it::
        
            $ mkc $PROJECT_NAME
            $ mkc $PROJECT_NAME -o $PROJECT_DIR
        
        
        Use --help/-h to view info on the arguments::
        
            $ mkc --help
            usage: mkc [-h] [--lib-name LIB_NAME] [--output-dir OUTPUT_DIR] name
        
            positional arguments:
              name
        
            optional arguments:
              -h, --help            show this help message and exit
              --lib-name LIB_NAME, -l LIB_NAME
              --output-dir OUTPUT_DIR, -o OUTPUT_DIR
        
        
        Release Notes
